article.headline: New Mexico 60, San Diego State 50
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Marcus Slaughter and John Sharper each scored 12 points Thursday as San Diego State held off a St. Xavier comeback and won 60-50 in exhibition play. Slaughter, a junior forward, added seven rebounds and five blocked shots. Sharper, a senior guard, also had eight rebounds. The Aztecs led 32-25 at halftime, building a 56-34 lead with 6:33 to play. St. Xavier of Chicago began a 16-4 run, but San Diego held on for the win. Jason Reiter led St. Xavier with 13 points. The Aztecs open the regular season Nov. 17 against Alaska Fairbanks.
